[SPEAKER_13]: Northbound vehicles and pedestrians cannot see each other when pedestrians are crossing from the Chevalier side.

906
01:16:16,749 --> 01:16:22,654
[SPEAKER_13]: This intersection is focal due to its proximity to the Chevalier Theatre, YMCA, bus stop, post office, and daycare.

907
01:16:22,674 --> 01:16:27,137
[SPEAKER_13]: Many thanks to Rector Brake for addressing the safety concerns surrounding this intersection.

908
01:16:27,657 --> 01:16:29,419
[SPEAKER_13]: He wholeheartedly supports this proposal.

909
01:16:29,939 --> 01:16:31,440
[SPEAKER_13]: And then for me, I do as well.

910
01:16:31,580 --> 01:16:38,886
[SPEAKER_13]: I know that there's been an improvement already from blocking the illegal parking space next to the entrance to the Chevalier.

911
01:16:41,158 --> 01:16:53,048
[SPEAKER_13]: parking lot and it seems to me that this additional intervention will just help maintain even better sight lines between folks trying to cross the street and cars because the traffic back up there is such a frequent occurrence.

912
01:16:54,409 --> 01:16:54,689
[SPEAKER_13]: Thank you.

913
01:16:56,150 --> 01:16:56,491
[SPEAKER_05]: Thank you.

914
01:16:56,511 --> 01:16:58,913
[SPEAKER_05]: Thank you for participating in the comments.

915
01:16:59,273 --> 01:17:03,176
[SPEAKER_05]: We did, the traffic commission did receive the email late this afternoon.

916
01:17:03,236 --> 01:17:06,439
[SPEAKER_05]: We will forward it to the commissioners, but we will make it part of the records.

917
01:17:06,479 --> 01:17:09,161
[SPEAKER_05]: We have a hard copy of that on file.

918
01:17:09,569 --> 01:17:13,571
[SPEAKER_05]: Is there anyone else here present who wishes to speak on this petition?

919
01:17:15,472 --> 01:17:16,372
[SPEAKER_05]: Just raise your hand.

920
01:17:18,313 --> 01:17:22,516
[SPEAKER_05]: Outside of public access, commissioners, any questions, comments?

921
01:17:28,719 --> 01:17:29,539
[SPEAKER_05]: Commissioner Brzezinski.

922
01:17:30,780 --> 01:17:31,200
[SPEAKER_03]: I love it.

923
01:17:31,760 --> 01:17:36,082
[SPEAKER_03]: You know, on many a concert night, this is a very dangerous area.

924
01:17:36,302 --> 01:17:38,624
[SPEAKER_03]: And I do see the parents who,

925
01:17:40,713 --> 01:17:44,375
[SPEAKER_03]: kind of fight back and forth to get across the street to the daycare, so I love it.

926
01:17:45,236 --> 01:17:52,920
[SPEAKER_03]: The only concern I have is we do have a box at the end of Forest Street that most of the paint is gone.

927
01:17:52,940 --> 01:18:05,427
[SPEAKER_03]: I just want to make sure that, I don't know, I think this is more of a systemic problem that once we draw it, we have a standard timeline where we go back in and continue to update the lines as they wear off.

928
01:18:05,527 --> 01:18:07,309
[SPEAKER_03]: But I fully support this.

929
01:18:07,389 --> 01:18:09,130
[SPEAKER_03]: Anything that makes it a little bit safer over there

930
01:18:09,994 --> 01:18:10,595
[SPEAKER_03]: is a good thing.

931
01:18:10,615 --> 01:18:16,039
[SPEAKER_05]: The chair appreciates your comments and agrees with them.

932
01:18:16,479 --> 01:18:17,840
[SPEAKER_05]: Commissioner McGiven, do you want to go next?

933
01:18:17,920 --> 01:18:23,765
[SPEAKER_18]: I don't have any comments on this, but I would just respond to Steve.

934
01:18:23,865 --> 01:18:26,027
[SPEAKER_18]: When we put down paint something like this, it's new.

935
01:18:26,507 --> 01:18:28,329
[SPEAKER_18]: The plan would be to refresh it.

936
01:18:28,869 --> 01:18:33,613
[SPEAKER_18]: And I acknowledge that there are places around the city that need refreshing.

937
01:18:34,293 --> 01:18:36,015
[SPEAKER_18]: So we're actively trying to get

938
01:18:36,914 --> 01:18:37,734
[SPEAKER_18]: paying crews out there.

939
01:18:38,895 --> 01:18:44,399
[SPEAKER_18]: So, and anyway, more assets we have on the road, the more that requires.

940
01:18:44,679 --> 01:18:49,642
[SPEAKER_18]: So, and if folks are in tune with the whole situation in Medford, it makes it tricky right now.

941
01:18:49,682 --> 01:18:52,463
[SPEAKER_18]: So anyway, we will do the best we can and we are on it.

942
01:18:53,824 --> 01:18:54,805
[SPEAKER_18]: And I support this also.

943
01:18:55,561 --> 01:18:57,682
[SPEAKER_05]: Thank you, Commissioner Brzezinski, your hand is back up.

944
01:18:57,702 --> 01:18:59,143
